item.title: SoftMatch: Addressing the Quantity-Quality Trade-off in Semi-supervised Learning
item.description: The critical challenge of Semi-Supervised Learning (SSL) is how to effectively leverage the limited labeled data and massive unlabeled data to improve the model's generalization performance.

item.title: Graph-based Recommendation for Sparse and Heterogeneous User Interactions
item.description: We propose a graph-based recommender model which utilizes heterogeneous interactions between users and content of different types and is able to operate well on small-scale datasets.

item.title: Revisiting Temporal Modeling for CLIP-based Image-to-Video Knowledge Transferring
item.description: In this paper, based on the CLIP model, we revisit temporal modeling in the context of image-to-video knowledge transferring, which is the key point for extending image-text pretrained models to the video domain.

item.description: Entities and events have long been regarded as the crux of machine reasoning.

item.description: In this paper, we develop SemSup-XC, a model that achieves state-of-the-art zero-shot and few-shot performance on three XC datasets derived from legal, e-commerce, and Wikipedia data.

item.title: Cut and Learn for Unsupervised Object Detection and Instance Segmentation
item.description: We propose Cut-and-LEaRn (CutLER), a simple approach for training unsupervised object detection and segmentation models.

item.title: Box$^2$EL: Concept and Role Box Embeddings for the Description Logic EL++
item.description: Representation learning in the form of semantic embeddings has been successfully applied to a variety of tasks in natural language processing and knowledge graphs.

item.title: Detecting Building Changes with Off-Nadir Aerial Images
item.description: The tilted viewing nature of the off-nadir aerial images brings severe challenges to the building change detection (BCD) problem: the mismatch of the nearby buildings and the semantic ambiguity of the building facades.

item.title: Graph Contrastive Learning for Skeleton-based Action Recognition
item.description: In this paper, we propose a graph contrastive learning framework for skeleton-based action recognition (\textit{SkeletonGCL}) to explore the \textit{global} context across all sequences.

item.title: Learning from Multiple Independent Advisors in Multi-agent Reinforcement Learning
item.description: This paper considers the problem of simultaneously learning from multiple independent advisors in multi-agent reinforcement learning.

item.title: The Projection-Enhancement Network (PEN)
item.description: Contemporary approaches to instance segmentation in cell science use 2D or 3D convolutional networks depending on the experiment and data structures.

item.description: (3) In contrast to a bridge that only contains token-wise self-attention, we propose a Dual Transformer Bridge that also includes channel-wise self-attention to exploit correlations between scales at different stages from a dual perspective.

item.title: Salesforce CausalAI Library: A Fast and Scalable Framework for Causal Analysis of Time Series and Tabular Data
item.description: We introduce the Salesforce CausalAI Library, an open-source library for causal analysis using observational data.

item.title: DEJA VU: Continual Model Generalization For Unseen Domains
item.description: To overcome these limitations of DA and DG in handling the Unfamiliar Period during continual domain shift, we propose RaTP, a framework that focuses on improving models' target domain generalization (TDG) capability, while also achieving effective target domain adaptation (TDA) capability right after training on certain domains and forgetting alleviation (FA) capability on past domains.

item.title: The Clinical Trials Puzzle: How Network Effects Limit Drug Discovery
item.description: The depth of knowledge offered by post-genomic medicine has carried the promise of new drugs, and cures for multiple diseases.

item.title: One Model for All Domains: Collaborative Domain-Prefix Tuning for Cross-Domain NER
item.description: Previous typical solutions mainly obtain a NER model by pre-trained language models (PLMs) with data from a rich-resource domain and adapt it to the target domain.

item.title: Editing Language Model-based Knowledge Graph Embeddings
item.description: We build four new datasets: E-FB15k237, A-FB15k237, E-WN18RR, and A-WN18RR, and evaluate several knowledge editing baselines demonstrating the limited ability of previous models to handle the proposed challenging task.

item.title: Feature Selection: Key to Enhance Node Classification with Graph Neural Networks
item.description: Graphs help to define the relationships between entities in the data.

item.title: ExaRanker: Explanation-Augmented Neural Ranker
item.description: Recent work has shown that inducing a large language model (LLM) to generate explanations prior to outputting an answer is an effective strategy to improve performance on a wide range of reasoning tasks.

item.title: Transfer Learning in Deep Learning Models for Building Load Forecasting: Case of Limited Data
item.description: In order to adapt Deep Learning models for buildings with limited and scarce data, this paper proposes a Building-to-Building Transfer Learning framework to overcome the problem and enhance the performance of Deep Learning models.

item.title: 3D Tooth Mesh Segmentation with Simplified Mesh Cell Representation
item.description: Summarizing of the mesh cell/triangle in this manner imposes an implicit structural constraint and makes it difficult to work with multiple resolutions which is done in many point cloud based deep learning algorithms.

item.title: SWING: Balancing Coverage and Faithfulness for Dialogue Summarization
item.description: Missing information is a common issue of dialogue summarization where some information in the reference summaries is not covered in the generated summaries.

item.title: Data Consistent Deep Rigid MRI Motion Correction
item.description: Motion artifacts are a pervasive problem in MRI, leading to misdiagnosis or mischaracterization in population-level imaging studies.

item.title: Improving Graph Generation by Restricting Graph Bandwidth
item.description: However, one of the main limitations of existing methods is their large output space, which limits generation scalability and hinders accurate modeling of the underlying distribution.

item.title: An Efficient Approximate Method for Online Convolutional Dictionary Learning
item.description: Most existing convolutional dictionary learning (CDL) algorithms are based on batch learning, where the dictionary filters and the convolutional sparse representations are optimized in an alternating manner using a training dataset.

item.title: Automated multilingual detection of Pro-Kremlin propaganda in newspapers and Telegram posts
item.description: The full-scale conflict between the Russian Federation and Ukraine generated an unprecedented amount of news articles and social media data reflecting opposing ideologies and narratives.

item.title: MLPGradientFlow: going with the flow of multilayer perceptrons (and finding minima fast and accurately)
item.description: MLPGradientFlow is a software package to solve numerically the gradient flow differential equation $\dot \theta = -\nabla \mathcal L(\theta; \mathcal D)$, where $\theta$ are the parameters of a multi-layer perceptron, $\mathcal D$ is some data set, and $\nabla \mathcal L$ is the gradient of a loss function.

item.title: Exact and rapid linear clustering of networks with dynamic programming
item.description: We study the problem of clustering networks whose nodes have imputed or physical positions in a single dimension, such as prestige hierarchies or the similarity dimension of hyperbolic embeddings.

item.title: When Layers Play the Lottery, all Tickets Win at Initialization
item.description: In this work, we investigate LTH and pruning at initialization from the lens of layer pruning.

item.title: Optimal decision making in robotic assembly and other trial-and-error tasks
item.description: Uncertainty in perception, actuation, and the environment often require multiple attempts for a robotic task to be successful.

item.title: Multi-Tenant Optimization For Few-Shot Task-Oriented FAQ Retrieval
item.description: Business-specific Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ) retrieval in task-oriented dialog systems poses unique challenges vis-\`a-vis community based FAQs.

item.title: Faster DAN: Multi-target Queries with Document Positional Encoding for End-to-end Handwritten Document Recognition
item.description: Recent advances in handwritten text recognition enabled to recognize whole documents in an end-to-end way: the Document Attention Network (DAN) recognizes the characters one after the other through an attention-based prediction process until reaching the end of the document.

item.title: ViDeBERTa: A powerful pre-trained language model for Vietnamese
item.description: This paper presents ViDeBERTa, a new pre-trained monolingual language model for Vietnamese, with three versions - ViDeBERTa_xsmall, ViDeBERTa_base, and ViDeBERTa_large, which are pre-trained on a large-scale corpus of high-quality and diverse Vietnamese texts using DeBERTa architecture.

item.title: E(n)-equivariant Graph Neural Cellular Automata
item.description: Cellular automata (CAs) are computational models exhibiting rich dynamics emerging from the local interaction of cells arranged in a regular lattice.

item.title: Recursive deep learning framework for forecasting the decadal world economic outlook
item.description: Due to the diversity and complexity of the world economy, a wide range of models have been used, but there are challenges in making decadal GDP forecasts given unexpected changes such as pandemics and wars.
